{"index": 564, "title": "IT Support Engineer", "job_location": "Glasgow, Scotland, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "A well-established organisation in Glasgow is looking for an IT Support Engineer to join the IT team (hybrid).This is an exciting opportunity to provide high-quality first and second line support to internal users, helping to ensure the smooth operation of business-critical systems and a great end-user experience.What You\u2019ll Be Doing:You\u2019ll be at the heart of the organisation\u2019s day-to-day IT operations, acting as a go-to expert for technical support across desktops, laptops, mobile devices. From onboarding new starters and provisioning equipment to diagnosing complex faults and resolving incidents, you\u2019ll take real ownership of issues from start to finish. You\u2019ll monitor and respond to alerts across modern security and cloud platforms such as Sophos, Zscaler, Azure and Microsoft 365, ensuring systems remain secure, stable and efficient. Working both on-site and remotely, you\u2019ll collaborate with colleagues and third-party suppliers to troubleshoot issues, maintain hardware and software, and continuously improve IT services. This is a hands-on, varied role where no two days are the same so it\u2019s ideal for someone who enjoys problem-solving, supporting people and making a visible impact.You\u2019ll ideally have most of the following:You\u2019ll be a confident and customer-focused IT support professional who thrives in a busy support environment. You\u2019ll be comfortable managing your own workload while working collaboratively as part of a wider team, and you\u2019ll deliver a professional service to users with varying levels of technical ability.** An IT-related qualification and/or relevant higher education** Hands-on technical support experience ** Experience supporting Microsoft-based environments** Experience working with / in an Azure environment ** Strong troubleshooting, communication and organisational skills.** Val